readme: ## is-nil-x Checks if `value` is `null` or `undefined`. ### `module.exports(value)` ⇒ boolean ⏏ Checks if `value` is `null` or `undefined`. **Kind**: Exported function **Returns**: boolean - Returns `true` if `value` is nullish, else `false`. | Param | Type | Description | | ----- | --------------- | ------------------- | | value | \* | The value to check. | **Example** ```js import isNil from 'is-nil-x'; console.log(isNil(null)); // => true console.log(isNil(void 0)); // => true console.log(isNil(NaN)); // => false ```
